##The sounds of the village

WECHAT denganqing1984

Feature description, here, I will share my writing, reading the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Woke up at 4:00 in the morning, day after day. It's not the insomnia, it's the Cock Crow. One could hear a cock crowing, and a loud voice coiled itself in the still night, and for a long time it did not go away; and after a moment of patience another cock crowed and answered. It's like they're having a lonely conversation.

Listen, listen, I went to sleep again, and at six o'clock I woke up again, this time the cock crow was nowhere to be found, and it was no longer just one or two. Jojo. Doot-doot. Throw it! Throw it. Gobble, gobble, Gobble. Ta-da-da. BOOP, boop, boop. Florida. Florida. No longer a place, but a room that surrounds me, in all directions.

Gradually, there began to be a voice, sounded each other on the embankment, "Get up? " "To the Vegetable Garden? " "There is a child under the pond washing clothes pop? " The mother also got up, the familiar footsteps, sounded downstairs.

It's past 7:00. I should get up. Dressed, washed, the living room and room windows are open, a cool breeze slowly pouring in. Looking out of the window, the garden and the wheat field were frosted White, and the sparrows were chasing each other on the red-tiled roof.

I almost forgot about the epidemic, as if in this small village, life will not be affected, still stretch forward. But in the morning the noise died down. Once again, everyone is in their homes.

When the sun is Shining, young people sit at the door, swiping their mobile phones, while older generations sit in their rooms and watch TV. The city has begun to restrict people from entering and leaving at will, and village officials have begun to urge people not to congregate on the embankment, even though it is not so strict. Patrols have also been posted at the entrance to the embankment, so cars and people are not allowed in or out.
Unable to return to Beijing, I had to take care of business at home. Sometimes I will think of the days in Beijing, it is also more than seven o'clock to get up, wash gargle to take the subway, the intermediate transfer once, out of the subway entrance, then take the bus.
When I used to come to the office, not many people came. Sitting at his desk, watching the elderly people across the residential building drying just washed clothes. One by one, the colleagues all came, calling one another, and the day began in earnest.
Such scenes come to mind from time to time. Do I miss living in Beijing for nine years? There, it's a different kind of rhythm to life. I weave my work, my friends, my interests into a personal world that is unique to me. But as I stayed at home, the world seemed further and further away from me.

Every year I come home as a guest, staying for a few days and then leaving. Now, I'm sitting in my room, watching the sun move slowly from side to side, the laundry on the balcony blowing in the wind. Talking about Beijing again at this time seems like an old dream.

In the afternoon, the polder began to be lively again, not because of the crowd, but because of the singing next door. Uncle's family can sing Karaoke, and at two or three in the afternoon, no accident, in Uncle's house on the second floor will be heard cousin lover's singing: "the sound of the waves still" , "holding hands" , "star language wish" , "the most dazzling national style" ... one after another, for two hours, without breathing.
Sometimes I hear someone call me, and as soon as I turn my head to look out of the window, another cousin's child across the street shouts at me, "uncle Qing, are you bored? I'll play the harmonica for you to get a kiss? " I haven't said anything yet, he started blowing, and I heard Twinkle Twinkle Little Star. Cousin in the inside said: "Do not disturb your uncle work. " The child said: "What people say, uncle clearly heard very fascinated! "
When the singing and the music stopped, the dike was once again calm. At six o'clock in the afternoon, when the sun was setting and the sunset was setting, the Crimson clouds were floating on the horizon of the opposite embankment, and more people began to walk along the road. Those who had been shut up for a day began to walk in twos and threes to the entrance of the dike.

On the other side of the provincial road, several small supermarkets opened their doors. Rice, noodles, oil and vegetables were the most sought-after. Everyone wore masks, picked out what they wanted to buy and haggled over the bill. Everyone was excited at that time, because almost a day did not talk to others, So said a lot.
By the time I came out with my hands full, it was completely dark. The street lamps in the polders lit up one by one, and the white light sprinkled on the empty road surface. When everyone had gone home, the door was shut, and a great silence began to cover the earth. The occasional dog barks. Another day passed.

Early in the morning, the garden was hoar.

I move where the sun shines.
The cousin's child is playing the Harmonica.
